Name: Peptide
Role: crucial regulators of various bodily functions, including metabolism, growth, stress responses, and reproduction, by binding to receptors on target cells and initiating intracellular signaling pathways

Name: Estrogen
Role: a sex hormone primarily known for its role in female sexual and reproductive health

Name: Progestogen
Role: prepares the uterus for pregnancy and maintains it during pregnancy

Name: Secosteroid
Role: an important regulator of calcium homeostasis and bone metabolism via actions in the intestine, bone, kidney, and parathyroid glands
